<p>In the newly created helper method, Matt introduced his desired change, 
which is much easier to understand in isolation than it would have been in the 
original <code>build_image_object</code> method definition. In particular, he changed
the duck typing test to look for <code>rewind</code> rather than <code>read</code>, in the hopes
that it would be a more reliable way to detect I/O-like objects. Everything 
else would be wrapped in a <code>Pathname</code> instance:</p>

